    "body" : "No, @MarkRotteveel it is NOT a duplicate of the question you have linked to.  The problem here is that the OP wants a timestamp.  They want to print that timestamp in UTC, without taking into account their system timezone or any other.  In other words, they want to have an <code>java.time.Instant</code>, but the API that they have to use is returning a <code>java.util.Date</code> instead.  If you could find a question which was &quot;how do I convert a <code>Date</code> into an <code>Instant</code>&quot;, then this would be a duplicate of THAT one."
