    "question_id" : 79704777,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>As far as I can tell, the default implementation of <code>Date</code> does not offer any ability to configure this out-of-the-box.</p>\n<p>However, if what the third-party code does is simply calling <code>toString()</code> on the <code>Date</code> instance, you can create your own <code>class MyBetterDate extends Date</code> subclass where you override the <code>toString()</code> method to present the value in whatever way you want.</p>\n"
